trailingComments.value:
*
 * Scale value by m, checking for overflow.
 * This has a short name to make above covaluee more reavalueable.
 * @param {Number|String} value
 * @param {Number} m
 * @param {Number} over
 * @return {Number}

leadingComments.value:
*
 * Scale value by m, checking for overflow.
 * This has a short name to make above covaluee more reavalueable.
 * @param {Number|String} value
 * @param {Number} m
 * @param {Number} over
 * @return {Number}

trailingComments.value: return x(valueInMicros, C1 / C0, MAX / (C1 / C0));

leadingComments.value: return x(valueInMicros, C1 / C0, MAX / (C1 / C0));

trailingComments.value: return x(valueInMillis, C2 / C0, MAX / (C2 / C0));

leadingComments.value: return x(valueInMillis, C2 / C0, MAX / (C2 / C0));
return x(valueInMillis, C2 / C1, MAX / (C2 / C1));

trailingComments.value: return x(valueInSeconds, C3 / C0, MAX / (C3 / C0));

leadingComments.value: return x(valueInSeconds, C3 / C0, MAX / (C3 / C0));
return x(valueInSeconds, C3 / C1, MAX / (C3 / C1));
return x(valueInSeconds, C3 / C2, MAX / (C3 / C2));

trailingComments.value: return x(valueInMinutes, C4 / C0, MAX / (C4 / C0));

leadingComments.value: return x(valueInMinutes, C4 / C0, MAX / (C4 / C0));
return x(valueInMinutes, C4 / C1, MAX / (C4 / C1));
return x(valueInMinutes, C4 / C2, MAX / (C4 / C2));
return x(valueInMinutes, C4 / C3, MAX / (C4 / C3));
return x(valueInHours, C5 / C1, MAX / (C5 / C1));
return x(valueInHours, C5 / C2, MAX / (C5 / C2));
return x(valueInHours, C5 / C3, MAX / (C5 / C3));
return x(valueInHours, C5 / C4, MAX / (C5 / C4));
